  "title": "Aesthetics Doctor 9am-6pm@Raffles Place (Preceptorship training by 20+ year experienced senior aesthetic doctor)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Structured Perceptorship | Up to S$40K/month | Professional Development | Retail Hours</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Opportunity Overview</strong><br />Join the SGP Healthcare Group, a leading aesthetics chain with presence in Singapore, Shanghai, Hangzhou, and Kuala Lumpur. We welcome passionate doctors who are committed to grow with us, a Singapore’s foremost medical aesthetic chain.</p><p>SGP Healthcare offers our young promising doctors a unique opportunity: a safe and guided environment to learn on the job, which is the only way your <strong>Certificates of Competence (COCs) </strong>can be transformed into practical skills and knowledge that make impacts on your patients.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>SGP Healthcare also has one of the widest selections of treatment providing on-the-job traineeship for every one of the 16 CoC categories.</strong> <strong>At SGP Healthcare you will help your patients in their pursuit of wellness and beauty to stay young and confident at any age.</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Why Join Us</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Attractive remuneration:</strong> Up to S$40K/month</li><li><strong>Comprehensive and Structured perceptorship training</strong> led by experienced doctor with 20 years of extensive experience in aesthetic dermatology — <em>no prior aesthetics experience required</em></li><li><strong>Flexible options:</strong> Full-time or part-time (from 24 hrs/week) with work-life balance</li><li><strong>Working Schedule</strong>: up to 5 workday per week</li><li><strong>Career growth:</strong> MOHH doctors welcome; bond transfer options discussed during interview</li><li><strong>Professional development Opportunities:</strong> Sponsorships for courses, conferences, and overseas assignments opportunities</li></ul><p><strong>Your Role</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct consultations and develop tailored treatment plans</li><li>Perform medical-grade aesthetic procedures</li><li>Collaborate with healthcare teams to optimise patient outcomes</li><li>Support research and development of new treatment programs</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Fully registered with the Singapore Medical Council (SMC)</li><li>MBBS or equivalent from a recognised institution</li><li>Relevant COCs preferred</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills; bilingual (English & Mandarin) preferred as role requires to consult our Chinese-speaking customer base</li></ul><p>📋 <strong>Application:</strong><br />Complete the form before applying:<br /><a href=\"https://forms.gle/BANHb1kAYwBY7k6D8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><u>https://forms.gle/BANHb1kAYwBY7k6D8</u><br /><br /><u></u></a>Please be informed that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
